BRIEFING: DEPT GATE: D33 / ARR GATE: 23 (GATE(S) ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE) PAX COUNTS: F 16 / Y 148 / NR 19 (PAX COUNTS ARE PRELIMINARY)
KLAS: LIGHT WINDS UNDER 8 KNOTS WILL FOLLOW DIURNAL WIND PATTERNS THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING. VFR CONDITIONS WILL PREVAIL WITH A FEW PASSING HIGH CLOUDS WITH BASES AOA 20KFT AGL, AND NO OPERATIONAL IMPACTS ARE ANTICIPATED.
ENRTE: EXPECT POSSIBLE CHOP/TURB FROM DEPT. A WEST TO EAST JTST ACROSS THE PACIFIC BEGINS TO EFFECT FLTS FROM W130 TO W145 HEADING ACROSS TRACKS.
HAWAIIAN ISLANDS: A COMBINATION OF EASTERLY WINDS AND SEA BREEZES WILL AFFECT EACH ISLAND ON SUNDAY WITH CLOUDS BUILDING OVER MOUNTAIN AND INTERIOR SECTIONS IN THE AFTERNOON HOURS.
THREAT SPACE WEATHER: NONE
NOTAMS PLEASE REVIEW NOTAMS SECTION OF PACKET FOR MOST CURRENT INFORMATION
